SIMPLE: madness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Madness
<hw>Mad"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Mad</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition of being mad;
insanity; lunacy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Frenzy; ungovernable rage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Extreme folly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Insanity; distraction; derangement; craziness;
lunacy; mania; frenzy; franticness; rage; aberration; alienation;
monomania. See <er>Insanity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madonna</ent>⟦br⟧
